title: Grand Ledge rises four spots in AP football poll
text:
Grand Ledge rises four spots in AP football poll Brian Calloway , Lansing State Journal 6:32 a.m. EDT October 13, 2015 Buy Photo Nolan Bird, Caden Evert and unbeaten Grand Ledge are up to No. 6 in Division 1 in this week's AP football poll. (Photo: MATTHEW DAE SMITH | for the Lansing State Journal) Buy Photo 
A week after moving into the top 10 in their respective divisions for the first time this fall, Grand Ledge and Corunna continued to climb up the state rankings. 
Grand Ledge moved up four spots and Corunna jumped two places in this week's Associated Press prep football poll, which is selected by a panel of sports reporters. 
CAAC Blue-leading Grand Ledge (7-0) moved up to No. 6 in Division 1, while GAC Red leader Corunna (6-1) is No. 8 in Division 4 in the latest rankings. 
CAAC White runner-up Lansing Catholic (6-1) and GLAC champion Lakewood (7-0) were the other area programs to move up in the poll this week. Lansing Catholic moved to No. 5 in Division 5 and Lakewood shares the No. 2 spot in Division 4 with Grand Rapids Catholic Central. 
Grand Ledge, Corunna, Lansing Catholic and Lakewood are among 10 mid-Michigan teams featured in the latest state poll heading into Week 8. 
Ithaca remains No. 1 in Division 6 to lead all area teams, while Portland is still No. 2 in Division 5. 
Other area teams in the top 10 include CAAC Red champion DeWitt (No. 4 in Division 3), CMAC leader Pewamo-Westphalia (No. 4 in Division 7) and Fowler (No. 7 in Division 8). 
Morrice, which is 6-1, is among the teams receiving votes just outside the top five in the 8-man division rankings. 
Contact Brian Calloway at bcalloway@lsj.com. Follow him on Twitter @brian_calloway.
